batchExecuteTransactions((uint256,uint25.details: Executes a batch of Exchange method calls in the context of signer(s).

params.signatures: Array of proofs that transactions have been signed by signer(s).

batchExecuteTransactions((uint256,uint25.return: returnData Array containing ABI encoded return data for each of the underlying Exchange function calls.

params.signatures: Proofs that orders have been created by makers.
params.takerAssetFillAmounts: Array of desired amounts of takerAsset to sell in orders.

batchFillOrKillOrders((address,address,a.return: fillResults Array of amounts filled and fees paid by makers and taker.

params.signatures: Proofs that orders have been created by makers.
params.takerAssetFillAmounts: Array of desired amounts of takerAsset to sell in orders.

batchFillOrders((address,address,address.return: fillResults Array of amounts filled and fees paid by makers and taker.

batchFillOrdersNoThrow((address,address,.details: Executes multiple calls of fillOrder. If any fill reverts, the error is caught and ignored.

params.signatures: Proofs that orders have been created by makers.
params.takerAssetFillAmounts: Array of desired amounts of takerAsset to sell in orders.

batchFillOrdersNoThrow((address,address,.return: fillResults Array of amounts filled and fees paid by makers and taker.

batchMatchOrders((address,address,addres.details: Match complementary orders that have a profitable spread.      Each order is filled at their respective price point, and      the matcher receives a profit denominated in the left maker asset.

params.leftOrders: Set of orders with the same maker / taker asset.
params.leftSignatures: Proof that left orders were created by the left makers.
params.rightOrders: Set of orders to match against `leftOrders`
params.rightSignatures: Proof that right orders were created by the right makers.

batchMatchOrders((address,address,addres.return: batchMatchedFillResults Amounts filled and profit generated.

batchMatchOrdersWithMaximalFill((address.details: Match complementary orders that have a profitable spread.      Each order is maximally filled at their respective price point, and      the matcher receives a profit denominated in either the left maker asset,      right maker asset, or a combination of both.

params.leftOrders: Set of orders with the same maker / taker asset.
params.leftSignatures: Proof that left orders were created by the left makers.
params.rightOrders: Set of orders to match against `leftOrders`
params.rightSignatures: Proof that right orders were created by the right makers.

batchMatchOrdersWithMaximalFill((address.return: batchMatchedFillResults Amounts filled and profit generated.

cancelOrder((address,address,address,add.details: After calling, the order can not be filled anymore.

cancelOrdersUpTo(uint256).details: Cancels all orders created by makerAddress with a salt less than or equal to the targetOrderEpoch      and senderAddress equal to msg.sender (or null address if msg.sender == makerAddress).

params.targetOrderEpoch: Orders created with a salt less or equal to this value will be cancelled.

constructor.details: Mixins are instantiated in the order they are inherited

params.chainId: Chain ID of the network this contract is deployed on.

detachProtocolFeeCollector().details: Sets the protocolFeeCollector contract address to 0.      Only callable by owner.

executeTransaction((uint256,uint256,uint.details: Executes an Exchange method call in the context of signer.

params.signature: Proof that transaction has been signed by signer.

executeTransaction((uint256,uint256,uint.return: ABI encoded return data of the underlying Exchange function call.

fillOrKillOrder((address,address,address.details: Fills the input order. Reverts if exact `takerAssetFillAmount` not filled.

params.signature: Proof that order has been created by maker.
params.takerAssetFillAmount: Desired amount of takerAsset to sell.

fillOrKillOrder((address,address,address.return: fillResults Amounts filled and fees paid.

params.signature: Proof that order has been created by maker.
params.takerAssetFillAmount: Desired amount of takerAsset to sell.

fillOrder((address,address,address,addre.return: fillResults Amounts filled and fees paid by maker and taker.

getAssetProxy(bytes4).return: assetProxy The asset proxy address registered to assetProxyId. Returns 0x0 if no proxy is registered.

getOrderInfo((address,address,address,ad.details: Gets information about an order: status, hash, and amount filled.
getOrderInfo((address,address,address,ad.return: orderInfo Information about the order and its state.         See LibOrder.OrderInfo for a complete description.

isValidHashSignature(bytes32,address,byt.details: Verifies that a hash has been signed by the given signer.

params.signature: Proof that the hash has been signed by signer.
params.signerAddress: Address that should have signed the given hash.

isValidHashSignature(bytes32,address,byt.return: isValid `true` if the signature is valid for the given hash and signer.

isValidOrderSignature((address,address,a.details: Verifies that a signature for an order is valid.

params.signature: Proof that the order has been signed by signer.

isValidOrderSignature((address,address,a.return: isValid `true` if the signature is valid for the given order and signer.

isValidTransactionSignature((uint256,uin.details: Verifies that a signature for a transaction is valid.

params.signature: Proof that the order has been signed by signer.

isValidTransactionSignature((uint256,uin.return: isValid `true` if the signature is valid for the given transaction and signer.

marketBuyOrdersFillOrKill((address,addre.details: Calls marketBuyOrdersNoThrow then reverts if < makerAssetFillAmount has been bought.      NOTE: This function does not enforce that the makerAsset is the same for each order.

params.makerAssetFillAmount: Minimum amount of makerAsset to buy.
params.signatures: Proofs that orders have been signed by makers.

marketBuyOrdersFillOrKill((address,addre.return: fillResults Amounts filled and fees paid by makers and taker.

marketBuyOrdersNoThrow((address,address,.details: Executes multiple calls of fillOrder until total amount of makerAsset is bought by taker.      If any fill reverts, the error is caught and ignored.      NOTE: This function does not enforce that the makerAsset is the same for each order.

params.makerAssetFillAmount: Desired amount of makerAsset to buy.
params.signatures: Proofs that orders have been signed by makers.

marketBuyOrdersNoThrow((address,address,.return: fillResults Amounts filled and fees paid by makers and taker.

marketSellOrdersFillOrKill((address,addr.details: Calls marketSellOrdersNoThrow then reverts if < takerAssetFillAmount has been sold.      NOTE: This function does not enforce that the takerAsset is the same for each order.

params.signatures: Proofs that orders have been signed by makers.
params.takerAssetFillAmount: Minimum amount of takerAsset to sell.

marketSellOrdersFillOrKill((address,addr.return: fillResults Amounts filled and fees paid by makers and taker.

marketSellOrdersNoThrow((address,address.details: Executes multiple calls of fillOrder until total amount of takerAsset is sold by taker.      If any fill reverts, the error is caught and ignored.      NOTE: This function does not enforce that the takerAsset is the same for each order.

params.signatures: Proofs that orders have been signed by makers.
params.takerAssetFillAmount: Desired amount of takerAsset to sell.

marketSellOrdersNoThrow((address,address.return: fillResults Amounts filled and fees paid by makers and taker.

matchOrders((address,address,address,add.details: Match two complementary orders that have a profitable spread.      Each order is filled at their respective price point. However, the calculations are      carried out as though the orders are both being filled at the right order's price point.      The profit made by the left order goes to the taker (who matched the two orders).

params.leftSignature: Proof that order was created by the left maker.
params.rightSignature: Proof that order was created by the right maker.

matchOrders((address,address,address,add.return: matchedFillResults Amounts filled and fees paid by maker and taker of matched orders.

matchOrdersWithMaximalFill((address,addr.details: Match two complementary orders that have a profitable spread.      Each order is maximally filled at their respective price point, and      the matcher receives a profit denominated in either the left maker asset,      right maker asset, or a combination of both.

params.leftSignature: Proof that order was created by the left maker.
params.rightSignature: Proof that order was created by the right maker.

matchOrdersWithMaximalFill((address,addr.return: matchedFillResults Amounts filled by maker and taker of matched orders.

preSign(bytes32).details: Approves a hash on-chain.      After presigning a hash, the preSign signature type will become valid for that hash and signer.

registerAssetProxy(address).details: Registers an asset proxy to its asset proxy id.      Once an asset proxy is registered, it cannot be unregistered.

params.assetProxy: Address of new asset proxy to register.

setProtocolFeeCollectorAddress(address).details: Allows the owner to update the protocolFeeCollector address.

setProtocolFeeMultiplier(uint256).details: Allows the owner to update the protocol fee multiplier.

setSignatureValidatorApproval(address,bo.details: Approves/unnapproves a Validator contract to verify signatures on signer's behalf      using the `Validator` signature type.

params.approval: Approval or disapproval of  Validator contract.

simulateDispatchTransferFromCalls(bytes[.details: This function may be used to simulate any amount of transfers As they would occur through the Exchange contract. Note that this function will always revert, even if all transfers are successful. However, it may be used with eth_call or with a try/catch pattern in order to simulate the results of the transfers.

params.amounts: Array containing the amounts that correspond to each transfer.
params.assetData: Array of asset details, each encoded per the AssetProxy contract specification.
params.fromAddresses: Array containing the `from` addresses that correspond with each transfer.
params.toAddresses: Array containing the `to` addresses that correspond with each transfer.

simulateDispatchTransferFromCalls(bytes[.return: This function does not return a value. However, it will always revert with `Error("TRANSFERS_SUCCESSFUL")` if all of the transfers were successful.

transferOwnership(address).details: Change the owner of this contract.
